cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper deals with supervised training of spiking neural networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the ReSuMe learning algorithm and its application to layered neural networks, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper explores the computational properties of spiking neural networks, which is a sub-field of AI. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the transformation of input spike trains into target output spike trains, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Although less likely, the paper does involve the encoding and transformation of information, which can be related to networking and internet architecture.
